        </div>
        <div class="day-toggle">+</div>
      </header>
      <div class="day-body">
        <p class="day-intro">Context windows are huge but not free. Context engineering = deciding what goes in the prompt, when, and how to compress what won't fit. Highest-leverage 2026 optimization.</p>

        
      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">Four pillars mastery</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Selection (what goes in), Compression (how to fit it), Ordering (where in prompt), Caching (what to keep across calls). Master these four and you cut costs 70%+.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://blog.langchain.dev/context-engineering-for-agents/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">Context Engineering for Agents (the manifesto)</span>
          <span class="resource-source">LangChain Blog</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        <a class="resource" href="https://rlancemartin.github.io/2025/06/23/context_engineering/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">The new prompt engineering is context engineering</span>
          <span class="resource-source">Lance Martin</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bullet-mini">
          <div class="bullet-mini-label">→ Hands-on</div>
          <p>Audit your day-4 RAG bot's full prompt. Categorize each piece into one of the 4 pillars. Identify the biggest waste.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">Context compression methods</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Summarize older turns. Extract only relevant fields from retrieved docs. Use a smaller model to compress before passing to the big one. LLMLingua-style prompt compression.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://python.langchain.com/docs/how_to/contextual_compression/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type docs">docs</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">LangChain Contextual Compression Retriever</span>
