          <span class="resource-source">LangChain Blog</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bullet-mini">
          <div class="bullet-mini-label">→ Hands-on</div>
          <p>Build a chat loop that keeps full history until total tokens > 4000. When exceeded, summarize the oldest 50% into one message and continue.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">Prompt caching hands-on</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Anthropic and OpenAI cache prompt prefixes. Cached input tokens cost ~10% of fresh ones. Massive savings on RAG and long system prompts.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
