    <article class="day" id="day-13">
      <header class="day-head">
        <div class="day-num-big">13</div>
        <div class="day-title-block">
          <div class="day-kicker">DAY 13 · WEEK 7</div>
          <div class="day-title">Personal Branding + Text-2-SQL</div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-toggle">+</div>
      </header>
      <div class="day-body">
        <p class="day-intro">Two skills bundled. The first — credibility on GitHub and LinkedIn — is how AI Eng jobs get found. The second — text-to-SQL — is one of the most-deployed AI features today.</p>

        
      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">LinkedIn positioning</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Your headline > your company. 'AI Engineer building RAG and agent systems' beats 'Software Engineer at X'. Posts and project demos beat resume bullets.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://www.latent.space/p/transitions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">How to position yourself as an AI Engineer</span>
          <span class="resource-source">swyx · Latent Space</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        <a class="resource" href="https://www.levels.fyi/blog/the-ultimate-guide-to-the-tech-resume.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">LinkedIn for engineers (no fluff)</span>
          <span class="resource-source">Levels.fyi Blog</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bullet-mini">
          <div class="bullet-mini-label">→ Hands-on</div>
          <p>Update your LinkedIn headline to position for AI Eng. Pin one of your projects. Write one short post about something you learned this week.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">GitHub portfolio storytelling</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Recruiters scan READMEs in 30 seconds. Open with the problem. Show a screenshot/gif. Then architecture. Then how to run. Pin 4-6 best repos.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://www.taniarascia.com/best-practices-for-the-readme-file/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">READMEs that get jobs</span>
          <span class="resource-source">Tania Rascia</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        <a class="resource" href="https://dev.to/scofieldidehen/what-do-recruiters-look-for-in-a-developers-github-3i52" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">What recruiters actually look at on GitHub</span>
          <span class="resource-source">DEV.to</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bullet-mini">
          <div class="bullet-mini-label">→ Hands-on</div>
          <p>Pick your strongest AI project. Rewrite its README with: problem, screenshot, architecture diagram, run instructions. Pin it on your GitHub profile.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">Text-2-SQL architecture</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Pattern: feed the LLM the schema (CREATE TABLE statements), the user question in English, and a few example queries. Get SQL back. Execute. Return result.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://python.langchain.com/docs/tutorials/sql_qa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type docs">docs</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">LangChain SQL agent tutorial</span>
          <span class="resource-source">LangChain Docs</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        <a class="resource" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L1o1VPVfbb0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type video">video</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">Text-to-SQL full build</span>
          <span class="resource-source">LangChain YouTube</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        <a class="resource" href="https://engineering.linkedin.com/blog/2024/practical-text-to-sql-for-data-analytics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">How LinkedIn built their text-to-SQL</span>
          <span class="resource-source">LinkedIn Engineering</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bullet-mini">
          <div class="bullet-mini-label">→ Hands-on</div>
          <p>Download the Chinook SQLite database. Build a text-to-SQL chain that answers 'Which 5 artists have the most tracks?' Print both the SQL it generated and the answer.</p>
