      <div class="day-body">
        <p class="day-intro">Once you have real traffic, the cost curve is a feature. Caching, routing, and Groq-style fast inference cut bills 5-10x with no quality loss.</p>

        
      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">Cost optimization at scale</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Levers: prompt caching, batching, smaller models, fewer retrievals, less in context. Track $/successful task, not $/token.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://www.anyscale.com/blog/llm-cost-optimization" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
          <span class="resource-title">How we cut our LLM bill 80%</span>
          <span class="resource-source">Anyscale Blog</span>
        </span>
        <span class="resource-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
        <a class="resource" href="https://eugeneyan.com/writing/llm-cost/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
        <span class="resource-info">
