      <div class="day-body">
        <p class="day-intro">Understanding RL fundamentals (especially GRPO behind DeepSeek-R1) plus thinking like a product person about which AI features deserve to exist.</p>

        
      <div class="bullet">
        <div class="bullet-header">
          <span class="bullet-arrow">→</span>
          <h3 class="bullet-heading">GRPO behind DeepSeek-R1</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="bullet-explain">Group Relative Policy Optimization — the technique that made DeepSeek-R1's reasoning gains possible. Skips the value model; uses group-mean reward. Cheaper than PPO.</p>

        <div class="bullet-section-label">Resources</div>
        <div class="resources">
        <a class="resource" href="https://magazine.sebastianraschka.com/p/the-state-of-llm-reasoning-model-training" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <span class="resource-type article">article</span>
